{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wf3cvy9oXD6nN38uGZcdMD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a developer,\n     9→I want a StackProvider interface that encapsulates all language-specific behavior,\n    10→So that adding a new language requires only one new file.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [x] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it defines `StackProvider` interface with: `name`, `markers`, `displayName`, `detectAppType()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `detectCoverageConfig()`, `getOtlpPackages()`, `installOtlp()`, `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`, `getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`, `getSemgrepLanguages()`, `parseTestOutput()`, `parseCoverageReport()`, `getProjectName()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC2: Given `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` exists, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it uses the registry's marker list (not hardcoded checks) to detect stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC3: Given the registry, when `getStackProvider('nodejs')` is called, then it returns the NodejsProvider instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    19→\n    20→- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/stacks/` directory\n    21→- [x] Task 2: Create `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Define `StackProvider` interface with all required methods/properties, plus supporting types: `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts`\n    22→- [x] Task 3: Create `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()` using provider marker arrays instead of hardcoded checks\n    23→- [x] Task 4: Create a minimal `NodejsProvider` stub in `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Implement enough of `StackProvider` to satisfy AC3 (returns correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`; other methods can throw `'not yet implemented'`)\n    24→- [x] Task 5: Create `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`\n    25→- [x] Task 6: Update `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` for backward compatibility (existing imports continue to work)\n    26→- [x] Task 7: Register `NodejsProvider` in registry (auto-registration in module initialization or explicit call)\n    27→- [x] Task 8: Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Cover: interface shape validation, registry `getStackProvider()`, registry `detectStacks()` using markers, backward compatibility of re-exports\n    28→\n    29→## Technical Notes\n    30→\n    31→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern)** drives this story. The interface must capture every method that currently varies by stack across the codebase.\n    32→\n    33→The `StackProvider` interface definition (from architecture-v3.md):\n    34→\n    35→```typescript\n    36→interface StackProvider {\n    37→  readonly name: StackName;\n    38→  readonly markers: string[];           // e.g., ['package.json']\n    39→  readonly displayName: string;         // e.g., 'Node.js (package.json)'\n    40→\n    41→  detectAppType(dir: string): AppType;\n    42→  getCoverageTool(): CoverageToolName;\n    43→  detectCoverageConfig(dir: string): CoverageToolInfo;\n    44→  getOtlpPackages(): string[];\n    45→  installOtlp(dir: string): OtlpResult;\n    46→  patchStartScript?(dir: string): boolean;\n    47→  getDockerfileTemplate(): string;\n    48→  getDockerBuildStage(): string;\n    49→  getRuntimeCopyDirectives(): string;\n    50→  getBuildCommands(): string[];\n    51→  getTestCommands(): string[];\n    52→  getSemgrepLanguages(): string[];\n    53→  parseTestOutput(output: string): TestCounts;\n    54→  parseCoverageReport(dir: string): number;\n    55→  getProjectName(dir: string): string | null;\n    56→}\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→The registry uses a `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` and detection iterates marker files via `fs.existsSync()` instead of the current hardcoded conditionals in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`.\n    60→\n    61→`detectStacks()` currently lives in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` with direct file checks. Move this logic to `registry.ts` where each registered provider's `markers` array is checked against the project directory.\n    62→\n    63→`StackName` and `AppType` types currently live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` (not `src/types/state.ts`). They should be moved to `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` and re-exported from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` for backward compatibility.\n    64→\n    65→### Important: Stub vs Full Provider\n    66→\n    67→AC3 requires `getStackProvider('nodejs')` to return a NodejsProvider instance. This means a minimal NodejsProvider must be created in this story (at least registered with correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`). Full method implementations happen in story 10-2.\n    68→\n    69→### Backward Compatibility\n    70→\n    71→`src/lib/stack-detect.ts` must continue exporting `StackName`, `AppType`, `detectStack()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectAppType()`, and `StackDetection` so existing consumers don't break. It can re-export from the new modules or keep its own implementation until story 10-5 migrates consumers.\n    72→\n    73→## Files to Change\n    74→\n    75→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Create. Define `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n    76→- `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Create. Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()`\n    77→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Create. Minimal `NodejsProvider` stub implementing `StackProvider` (full implementation in story 10-2)\n    78→- `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Create. Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`\n    79→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from stacks/types.ts for backward compatibility (deletion deferred to story 10-5)\n    80→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Create. Tests for types, registry, and detection\n    81→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KYHNjFyPBqtp8DZjE8JmLf","session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"0048ae7d-8b10-40d9-b640-1dece11ae9c1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:12:05.963Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E46cM6Wk1tR29GnauGQFzA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-2: Implement NodejsProvider\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a developer,\n     9→I want all Node.js-specific logic in one file,\n    10→So that Node.js behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [x] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` exists, when inspected, then it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Node.js: `detectAppType()` (server/cli/web/agent/generic from package.json), `getCoverageTool()` (returns `'c8'`), `detectCoverageConfig()` (vitest/jest/c8 detection from package.json devDependencies), `getOtlpPackages()` (returns `@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-node`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-http`), `installOtlp()` (runs `npm install`), `patchStartScript()` (adds `--require` flag to start/dev script), `getDockerfileTemplate()` (node:22-slim based), `getDockerBuildStage()` (multi-stage build snippet), `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` (COPY from build-nodejs), `getBuildCommands()` (`['npm install', 'npm run build']`), `getTestCommands()` (`['npm test']`), `getSemgrepLanguages()` (`['javascript', 'typescript']`), `parseTestOutput()` (vitest/jest format parsing), `parseCoverageReport()` (coverage-summary.json parsing), `getProjectName()` (reads package.json `name` field) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC2: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing `@vitest/coverage-v8` in devDependencies and a `vitest.config.ts` file, when `NodejsProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'c8' }` with a defined `configFile`, matching the behavior of the current `detectNodeCoverageTool()` in `coverage.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC3: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing `jest` in devDependencies, when `NodejsProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'c8' }` (Jest uses c8/istanbul underneath) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC4: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing `anthropic` in dependencies, when `NodejsProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'agent'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC5: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing `react` in dependencies, when `NodejsProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'web'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC6: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing a `bin` field and no `start` script, when `NodejsProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'cli'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [x] AC7: Given a temporary directory with a `package.json` containing a `start` script (no agent/web deps), when `NodejsProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→- [x] AC8: Given `NodejsProvider.getOtlpPackages()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns exactly `['@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node', '@opentelemetry/sdk-node', '@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http', '@opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-http']` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [x] AC9: Given `NodejsProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM node:22-slim`, `npm install -g`, and `USER node` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→- [x] AC10: Given `NodejsProvider.getDockerBuildStage()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM node:22-slim AS build-nodejs` and `npm ci --production` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→- [x] AC11: Given `NodejsProvider.getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `COPY --from=build-nodejs` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→- [x] AC12: Given vitest output text `Tests  12 passed | 3 failed`, when `NodejsProvider.parseTestOutput()` is called, then it returns `{ passed: 12, failed: 3, skipped: 0, total: 15 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→- [x] AC13: Given jest output text `Tests:  3 failed, 12 passed, 15 total`, when `NodejsProvider.parseTestOutput()` is called, then it returns `{ passed: 12, failed: 3, skipped: 0, total: 15 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→- [x] AC14: Given a directory with `coverage/coverage-summary.json` containing `{ \"total\": { \"statements\": { \"pct\": 85.5 } } }`, when `NodejsProvider.parseCoverageReport()` is called, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→- [x] AC15: Given a directory with a `package.json` containing `{ \"name\": \"my-app\" }`, when `NodejsProvider.getProjectName()` is called, then it returns `'my-app'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→- [x] AC16: Given `NodejsProvider.getSemgrepLanguages()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns `['javascript', 'typescript']` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→- [x] AC17: Given `NodejsProvider.getBuildCommands()` and `getTestCommands()` are called, when the results are inspected, then they return `['npm install', 'npm run build']` and `['npm test']` respectively <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    31→- [x] AC18: Given unit tests exist in `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts`, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    32→\n    33→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    34→\n    35→- [x] Task 1: Implement `NodejsProvider.detectAppType()` — Extract Node.js app type detection logic from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` `detectAppType()` (the `stack === 'nodejs'` branch). Read `package.json`, check deps for agent SDKs (anthropic, openai, langchain), web frameworks (react, vue, next), bin field (cli), start script (server), fallback to generic.\n    36→- [x] Task 2: Implement `NodejsProvider.getCoverageTool()` — Return `'c8'` as the canonical Node.js coverage tool.\n    37→- [x] Task 3: Implement `NodejsProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` — Extract from `coverage.ts` `detectNodeCoverageTool()`. Check for vitest config files, `@vitest/coverage-v8`, `@vitest/coverage-istanbul`, `c8`, `jest` in package.json devDependencies. Return `CoverageToolInfo` with `tool` and optional `configFile`.\n    38→- [x] Task 4: Implement `NodejsProvider.getOtlpPackages()` — Return the `NODE_OTLP_PACKAGES` array from `otlp.ts`: `@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-node`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-http`.\n    39→- [x] Task 5: Implement `NodejsProvider.installOtlp()` — Extract from `otlp.ts` `installNodeOtlp()`. Run `npm install` with the OTLP packages. Return `OtlpResult` with success/failure.\n    40→- [x] Task 6: Implement `NodejsProvider.patchStartScript()` — Extract from `otlp.ts` `patchNodeStartScript()`. Add `--require @opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node/register` to start/dev script in package.json.\n    41→- [x] Task 7: Implement `NodejsProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `nodejsTemplate()`. Return the node:22-slim Dockerfile string.\n    42→- [x] Task 8: Implement `NodejsProvider.getDockerBuildStage()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `nodejsBuildStage()`. Return multi-stage build snippet.\n    43→- [x] Task 9: Implement `NodejsProvider.getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `runtimeCopyDirectives()` (the nodejs branch). Return `COPY --from=build-nodejs` lines.\n    44→- [x] Task 10: Implement `NodejsProvider.getBuildCommands()` — Return `['npm install', 'npm run build']`.\n    45→- [x] Task 11: Implement `NodejsProvider.getTestCommands()` — Return `['npm test']`.\n    46→- [x] Task 12: Implement `NodejsProvider.getSemgrepLanguages()` — Return `['javascript', 'typescript']`.\n    47→- [x] Task 13: Implement `NodejsProvider.parseTestOutput()` — Extract vitest and jest parsing from `coverage.ts` `parseTestCounts()`. Vitest: `Tests  N passed | M failed`. Jest: `Tests:  M failed, N passed, T total`. Return `TestCounts`.\n    48→- [x] Task 14: Implement `NodejsProvider.parseCoverageReport()` — Extract from `coverage.ts` `parseVitestCoverage()`. Read `coverage/coverage-summary.json`, parse `total.statements.pct`. Also check `src/coverage/coverage-summary.json` as fallback.\n    49→- [x] Task 15: Implement `NodejsProvider.getProjectName()` — Extract from `docs-scaffold.ts` `getProjectName()`. Read `package.json` `name` field. Return `null` if not found.\n    50→- [x] Task 16: Create `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts` — Unit tests for every method. Use temp directories with fixture `package.json` files. Cover: each app type variant, coverage tool detection (vitest, jest, c8, none), test output parsing (vitest format, jest format, no match), coverage report parsing (valid JSON, missing file, malformed), project name (present, missing, no package.json), OTLP packages, Dockerfile content, build/test commands, semgrep languages.\n    51→- [x] Task 17: Verify the existing test suite still passes — run `npm test` and confirm 0 regressions.\n    52→\n    53→## Technical Notes\n    54→\n    55→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern).** This is the reference implementation — Python and Rust providers (stories 10-3, 10-4) follow the same pattern.\n    56→\n    57→### What moves INTO NodejsProvider\n    58→\n    59→| Method | Source File | Source Function/Branch |\n    60→|--------|------------|----------------------|\n    61→| `detectAppType()` | `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | `detectAppType()` → `stack === 'nodejs'` branch |\n    62→| `getCoverageTool()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `detectCoverageTool()` → `stack === 'nodejs'` branch |\n    63→| `detectCoverageConfig()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `detectNodeCoverageTool()` |\n    64→| `getOtlpPackages()` | `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `NODE_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant |\n    65→| `installOtlp()` | `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `installNodeOtlp()` |\n    66→| `patchStartScript()` | `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `patchNodeStartScript()` |\n    67→| `getDockerfileTemplate()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `nodejsTemplate()` |\n    68→| `getDockerBuildStage()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `nodejsBuildStage()` |\n    69→| `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `runtimeCopyDirectives()` nodejs branch |\n    70→| `getBuildCommands()` | `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | `generateAgentsMdContent()` nodejs branch |\n    71→| `getTestCommands()` | `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | `generateAgentsMdContent()` nodejs branch |\n    72→| `getSemgrepLanguages()` | New | `['javascript', 'typescript']` |\n    73→| `parseTestOutput()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `parseTestCounts()` vitest+jest branches |\n    74→| `parseCoverageReport()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `parseVitestCoverage()` |\n    75→| `getProjectName()` | `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | `getProjectName()` nodejs path |\n    76→\n    77→### Important: Do NOT remove consumer branches yet\n    78→\n    79→This story implements the provider methods only. Consumer files (`coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`) keep their existing if/else branches for now. Story 10-5 migrates consumers to use `provider.method()` and removes the branches. This avoids a big-bang migration.\n    80→\n    81→### Dependencies from `stack-detect.ts`\n    82→\n    83→The helper functions `readJsonSafe()`, `getNodeDeps()`, `readTextSafe()` in `stack-detect.ts` are used by the Node.js detection logic. Either:\n    84→1. Copy them into `nodejs.ts` (some duplication, cleaned up in 10-5), or\n    85→2. Extract into a shared `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` file\n    86→\n    87→Option 2 is preferred — a small `utils.ts` with `readJsonSafe()`, `readTextSafe()`, `getNodeDeps()` avoids duplication across providers.\n    88→\n    89→### Type mapping: `CoverageToolInfo`\n    90→\n    91→The `CoverageToolInfo` in `stacks/types.ts` has `{ tool: CoverageToolName; configFile?: string }`. The current `coverage.ts` `CoverageToolInfo` has `{ tool: string; runCommand: string; reportFormat: string }`. The provider's `detectCoverageConfig()` returns the stacks/types version. The `runCommand` and `reportFormat` can be derived from the tool name by the consumer or added to the provider as separate methods if needed during story 10-5.\n    92→\n    93→## Dev Notes\n    94→\n    95→- The `NodejsProvider` class already exists as a stub from story 10-1 with all methods throwing `'not yet implemented'`. Replace each stub with the real implementation.\n    96→- Registration in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` already calls `registerProvider(new NodejsProvider())` — no change needed there.\n    97→- `markers` and `displayName` are already set correctly from story 10-1.\n    98→\n    99→## Files to Change\n   100→\n   101→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Replace all stub methods with real implementations extracted from consumer files\n   102→- `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` — Create. Shared helpers: `readJsonSafe()`, `readTextSafe()`, `getNodeDeps()` (extracted from `stack-detect.ts`)\n   103→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts` — Create. Comprehensive unit tests for all NodejsProvider methods\n   104→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KYHNjFyPBqtp8DZjE8JmLf","session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"ef4ad6c2-d5de-4ad1-967c-6319c55a1c0c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:12:06.101Z"}
