ion must fire before any other parser -- this ordering guard is critical.\" In the provider pattern, each provider has its own `parseTestOutput()`, so there's no cross-provider ordering concern. The aggregation regex with global flag and iteration handles workspace output correctly within the Rust provider alone. No risk here.\n- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. Rust provider has no external system dependencies for unit testing since `installOtlp()` and `detectCoverageConfig()` (which shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` in the consumer) can be tested by mocking or by testing the file-reading path only. The provider's `detectCoverageConfig()` differs from the consumer's -- it reads Cargo.toml presence rather than executing `cargo tarpaulin --version`."}],"totalDurationMs":152671,"totalTokens":72640,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":172,"cache_read_input_tokens":71809,"output_tokens":658,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":172},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
