{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0198fVpqnTCszfWpp7XMVRBt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/lib/stacks — Stack Provider System\n     2→\n     3→Encapsulates per-language logic behind the `StackProvider` interface. Each provider implements detection, coverage, OTLP instrumentation, Dockerfile generation, and test parsing for one technology stack.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n     8→|------|---------|-------------|\n     9→| types.ts | Canonical type definitions — `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, coverage/OTLP/test types | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n    10→| registry.ts | Provider registry — registration, lookup, marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n    11→| nodejs.ts | Node.js provider — app type detection, coverage (c8/vitest/jest), OTLP packages, Dockerfile (node:22-slim), test output parsing | `NodejsProvider` |\n    12→| utils.ts | Shared helpers for providers — safe JSON/text reading, Node.js dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps` |\n    13→| index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n    14→\n    15→## Architecture\n    16→\n    17→- `StackProvider` interface in `types.ts` defines the contract (15 methods, 1 optional)\n    18→- Each stack gets its own file (`nodejs.ts`, future: `python.ts`, `rust.ts`)\n    19→- `registry.ts` stores providers in a module-level `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`\n    20→- `index.ts` triggers auto-registration on import\n    21→- `utils.ts` provides shared filesystem helpers used across providers\n    22→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"48da31fd-41b1-4a79-8ec3-a543cea21494","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:32:28.222Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/AGENTS.md","content":"# src/lib/stacks — Stack Provider System\n\nEncapsulates per-language logic behind the `StackProvider` interface. Each provider implements detection, coverage, OTLP instrumentation, Dockerfile generation, and test parsing for one technology stack.\n\n## Files\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| types.ts | Canonical type definitions — `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, coverage/OTLP/test types | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n| registry.ts | Provider registry — registration, lookup, marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n| nodejs.ts | Node.js provider — app type detection, coverage (c8/vitest/jest), OTLP packages, Dockerfile (node:22-slim), test output parsing | `NodejsProvider` |\n| utils.ts | Shared helpers for providers — safe JSON/text reading, Node.js dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps` |\n| index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n\n## Architecture\n\n- `StackProvider` interface in `types.ts` defines the contract (15 methods, 1 optional)\n- Each stack gets its own file (`nodejs.ts`, future: `python.ts`, `rust.ts`)\n- `registry.ts` stores providers in a module-level `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`\n- `index.ts` triggers auto-registration on import\n- `utils.ts` provides shared filesystem helpers used across providers\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
