{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EohDxuefQxaQnydZwz9WkS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-5: Migrate All Consumers to StackProvider\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want zero `if (stack === 'nodejs')` patterns outside `src/lib/stacks/`,\n     9→So that the stack abstraction doesn't leak.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`, `verify/env.ts`, `readme.ts`, when inspected, then zero stack string comparisons remain -- all use `provider.method()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a boundary test exists, when it scans `src/` for `stack === 'nodejs'` or `stack === 'python'` or `stack === 'rust'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`, then it finds zero matches <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern)** and **NFR4** (no direct stack conditionals outside `src/lib/stacks/`).\n    19→\n    20→This is the cleanup story after 10-1 through 10-4. Every remaining consumer of stack-specific logic must call through the provider interface.\n    21→\n    22→Consumer migration pattern:\n    23→```typescript\n    24→// Before\n    25→if (stack === 'nodejs') {\n    26→  tool = detectNodeCoverageTool(dir);\n    27→} else if (stack === 'python') {\n    28→  tool = 'coverage.py';\n    29→} else if (stack === 'rust') {\n    30→  tool = 'cargo-tarpaulin';\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→// After\n    34→const provider = getStackProvider(stack);\n    35→const tool = provider.detectCoverageConfig(dir);\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→Files to audit for remaining stack conditionals:\n    39→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Should delegate all detection/parsing to provider\n    40→- `src/lib/otlp.ts` — Should delegate package lists and install to provider\n    41→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Should use provider for build/test commands\n    42→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — Should use provider for Dockerfile generation\n    43→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Should use provider for verify Dockerfile sections\n    44→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — Should use provider for project name, commands\n    45→- `src/commands/stack.ts` — May legitimately reference stack names for display\n    46→- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — May need provider for semgrep language selection\n    47→\n    48→Write a boundary test at `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/boundary.test.ts` that:\n    49→1. Reads all `.ts` files in `src/` excluding `src/lib/stacks/`\n    50→2. Searches for patterns: `stack === 'nodejs'`, `stack === 'python'`, `stack === 'rust'`, `=== 'nodejs'`, `=== 'python'`, `=== 'rust'`\n    51→3. Fails if any matches found\n    52→\n    53→Also delete `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` since its logic now lives in `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts`. Update all imports.\n    54→\n    55→## Files to Change\n    56→\n    57→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Replace all stack conditionals with `getStackProvider(stack).method()` calls\n    58→- `src/lib/otlp.ts` — Replace all stack conditionals with provider calls\n    59→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Replace stack conditionals with `provider.getBuildCommands()`, `provider.getTestCommands()`\n    60→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — Replace stack conditionals with `provider.getDockerfileTemplate()`\n    61→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Replace stack conditionals with provider calls for verify Dockerfile generation\n    62→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — Replace stack conditionals with provider calls\n    63→- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — Replace stack conditionals with `provider.getSemgrepLanguages()`\n    64→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Delete. All callers import from `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` instead\n    65→- `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/boundary.test.ts` — Create. Boundary test enforcing NFR4\n    66→- All files importing from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Update imports to `src/lib/stacks/index.ts`\n    67→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016pVTiEDvkXc8fi67pKiZeQ","session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"14bc1eed-2fb5-4013-ac1a-d4c4807a1b25","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:35:29.831Z"}
