{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8NfupizpoA4jhKeCsJVu7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 10-4-rust-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:14Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Story notes mention `'library'` AppType for Rust, but `AppType` union in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` has no `'library'` variant — only `'generic'`. Followed actual code behavior (returns `'generic'`).\n     6→- **Bevy system libs:** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in current `dockerfile-template.ts`. Deferred to avoid scope creep.\n     7→- **Risk — workspace aggregation ordering:** No cross-provider ordering concern in the provider pattern; handled within Rust provider alone.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. No external system dependencies for unit testing.\n     9→\n    10→### 10-4-rust-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:24Z)\n    11→\n    12→No issues reported. 55/55 new tests pass, 3397/3397 total tests pass, no regressions.\n    13→\n    14→### 10-4-rust-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T09:34Z)\n    15→\n    16→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` — example was backwards.\n    17→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching (2 tests added).\n    18→- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies. Pre-existing behavior from `stack-detect.ts`.\n    19→- **LOW (not fixed):** `getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format. Pre-existing behavior.\n    20→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for `installOtlp` success path (requires `cargo` binary).\n    21→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"de13fbd1-70d6-4958-8ba6-d59b7a8479ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:38:13.650Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:14Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Story notes mention `'library'` AppType for Rust, but `AppType` union in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` has no `'library'` variant — only `'generic'`. Followed actual code behavior (returns `'generic'`).\n- **Bevy system libs:** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in current `dockerfile-template.ts`. Deferred to avoid scope creep.\n- **Risk — workspace aggregation ordering:** No cross-provider ordering concern in the provider pattern; handled within Rust provider alone.\n- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. No external system dependencies for unit testing.\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:24Z)\n\nNo issues reported. 55/55 new tests pass, 3397/3397 total tests pass, no regressions.\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T09:34Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` — example was backwards.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching (2 tests added).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies. Pre-existing behavior from `stack-detect.ts`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format. Pre-existing behavior.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for `installOtlp` success path (requires `cargo` binary).\n","numLines":21,"startLine":1,"totalLines":21}}}
