{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015RnPHKjMBkdLZaMfUZ9rts","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 10-4-rust-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:14Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Story notes mention `'library'` AppType for Rust, but `AppType` union in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` has no `'library'` variant — only `'generic'`. Followed actual code behavior (returns `'generic'`).\n     6→- **Bevy system libs:** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in current `dockerfile-template.ts`. Deferred to avoid scope creep.\n     7→- **Risk — workspace aggregation ordering:** No cross-provider ordering concern in the provider pattern; handled within Rust provider alone.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. No external system dependencies for unit testing.\n     9→\n    10→### 10-4-rust-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:24Z)\n    11→\n    12→No issues reported. 55/55 new tests pass, 3397/3397 total tests pass, no regressions.\n    13→\n    14→### 10-4-rust-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T09:34Z)\n    15→\n    16→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` — example was backwards.\n    17→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching (2 tests added).\n    18→- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies. Pre-existing behavior from `stack-detect.ts`.\n    19→- **LOW (not fixed):** `getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format. Pre-existing behavior.\n    20→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for `installOtlp` success path (requires `cargo` binary).\n    21→\n    22→### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:43Z)\n    23→\n    24→- **Risk:** AC17 (`verify-prompt.ts`) compares `AppType` not `StackName` — could false-positive boundary tests.\n    25→- **Risk:** AC16 (`teardown.ts`) accesses state field not local variable — migration needs state shape understanding.\n    26→- **Risk:** `detectAppType()` export chain may break if `stack-detect.ts` deleted before re-export verified.\n    27→- **Observation:** `otlp.ts` is heaviest migration target (~10 stack conditionals). `scanner.ts` had zero stack conditionals.\n    28→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UTpMQozhuu6pShveLAYi4N","session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"f69ad6d9-96ec-4c1c-8f1c-a3bbaa3a51ca","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:38:48.917Z"}
