{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DS4rNhZ4y4G5MrmAkSZ49m","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-4: Implement RustProvider\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: done\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a developer,\n     9→I want all Rust-specific logic in one file,\n    10→So that Rust behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [x] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts` exists, when inspected, then it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Rust: `detectAppType()` (agent/server/cli/generic from Cargo.toml `[dependencies]` section parsing, `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`), `getCoverageTool()` (returns `'tarpaulin'`), `detectCoverageConfig()` (checks for cargo-tarpaulin availability and workspace flag), `getOtlpPackages()` (returns `['opentelemetry', 'opentelemetry-otlp', 'tracing-opentelemetry', 'tracing-subscriber']`), `installOtlp()` (runs `cargo add` for all OTLP deps), `getDockerfileTemplate()` (multi-stage builder+runtime Dockerfile with rust:1.82-slim and debian:bookworm-slim), `getDockerBuildStage()` (returns `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS build-rust` stage), `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` (returns `COPY --from=build-rust` line), `getBuildCommands()` (`['cargo build', 'cargo test']`), `getTestCommands()` (`['cargo test']`), `getSemgrepLanguages()` (`['rust']`), `parseTestOutput()` (cargo test format with workspace aggregation), `parseCoverageReport()` (tarpaulin-report.json parsing), `getProjectName()` (reads `Cargo.toml` `[package] name`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC2: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing `[dependencies]` with `async-openai`, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'agent'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC3: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing `[dependencies]` with `actix-web`, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC4: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing `[dependencies]` with `axum`, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC5: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing `[dependencies]` with `rocket`, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC6: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing a `[[bin]]` section and no web framework deps, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'cli'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [x] AC7: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing a `[lib]` section and no `[[bin]]` section, when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'generic'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→- [x] AC8: Given a temporary directory with a minimal `Cargo.toml` (no `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`, or framework deps), when `RustProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'generic'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [x] AC9: Given `RustProvider.getCoverageTool()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns `'tarpaulin'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→- [x] AC10: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` (non-workspace), when `RustProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'tarpaulin' }` with a defined `configFile` pointing to Cargo.toml <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→- [x] AC11: Given a temporary directory with a `Cargo.toml` containing a `[workspace]` section, when `RustProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'tarpaulin' }` with a `configFile` pointing to Cargo.toml <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→- [x] AC12: Given a temporary directory without a `Cargo.toml`, when `RustProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'none' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→- [x] AC13: Given `RustProvider.getOtlpPackages()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns exactly `['opentelemetry', 'opentelemetry-otlp', 'tracing-opentelemetry', 'tracing-subscriber']` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→- [x] AC14: Given `RustProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder`, `cargo build --release`, `FROM debian:bookworm-slim`, and `USER nobody` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→- [x] AC15: Given `RustProvider.getDockerBuildStage()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS build-rust` and `cargo build --release` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→- [x] AC16: Given `RustProvider.getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `COPY --from=build-rust` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→- [x] AC17: Given cargo test output `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 1 ignored`, when `RustProvider.parseTestOutput()` is called, then it returns `{ passed: 42, failed: 3, skipped: 1, total: 46 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UTpMQozhuu6pShveLAYi4N","session_id":"1d547185-a995-481d-9659-9279ed70f717","uuid":"09914944-941e-497c-b9de-f08e9c653c5e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:39:12.965Z"}
